    },
    {
      "id": "4locisD2Ye-OYOJF6IZgy",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 12596.05217225191,
      "y": 6981.24215070745,
      "width": 326.459716796875,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "c0X3",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1316323398,
      "version": 149,
      "versionNonce": 2059316550,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773153291379,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "will generate a stealth public key ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "will generate a stealth public key ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "RUwJgLb4Q8gzsG_eUN8JY",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 12174.285413447165,
      "y": 6815.09023419427,
      "width": 580.8194580078125,
      "height": 575,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "c0X4",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1725151302,
      "version": 1093,
      "versionNonce": 1130964038,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773153503348,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. Sender will use receiver's stealth \npublic to generate a one-time \naddress\n\n2. sender will send the funds to that \naddress  \n\n3. receiver will scan the blockchain, for \nany address generated (if any) \n\n4. if there are then, he'll have the access \nto that address, in the form of \n\na. view key: to verify that the account belongs \n    to the recipent\n\nb. spend key: to actually spend those funds\n\n// so the distinction remains that we can argue,\n    that anyone can track that the sender generated \n    address is linked to the recipient address, but that \n    is not the case, I guess view key becomes important, if \n    that is compromised than the user is generally screwed ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. Sender will use receiver's stealth \npublic to generate a one-time \naddress\n\n2. sender will send the funds to that \naddress  \n\n3. receiver will scan the blockchain, for \nany address generated (if any) \n\n4. if there are then, he'll have the access \nto that address, in the form of \n\na. view key: to verify that the account belongs \n    to the recipent\n\nb. spend key: to actually spend those funds\n\n// so the distinction remains that we can argue,\n    that anyone can track that the sender generated \n    address is linked to the recipient address, but that \n    is not the case, I guess view key becomes important, if \n    that is compromised than the user is generally screwed ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
