    },
    {
      "id": "xsgRzRSDtasWMw00MEK2l",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 12156.494170200673,
      "y": 7578.196940870794,
      "width": 794.4393310546875,
      "height": 350,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "c0X9",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1848331802,
      "version": 1258,
      "versionNonce": 742973210,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773154039907,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "follow-up questions \n1. so does stealth address generation, works differently?\nlike they do not give a single address, instead they give \n2 keys (view key & spend key) instead of a single public \naddress? which is what wallets like Phantom & Metamask does \n\n2. so you said that receiver will scan the blockchain for every \ntransaction, doesn't this sound like something very much a big process? \nI mean how can receiver be scanning each & every transaction, and I \ncould mean that the receiver would be only scanning for specific transctions\nlike he actually has idea that B (receiver) is gonna receive money from A (sender)\nbut does not know that on what address he'll be receiving, so he'll keep scanning\nthat's the only possible idea I can think of right now \n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "follow-up questions \n1. so does stealth address generation, works differently?\nlike they do not give a single address, instead they give \n2 keys (view key & spend key) instead of a single public \naddress? which is what wallets like Phantom & Metamask does \n\n2. so you said that receiver will scan the blockchain for every \ntransaction, doesn't this sound like something very much a big process? \nI mean how can receiver be scanning each & every transaction, and I \ncould mean that the receiver would be only scanning for specific transctions\nlike he actually has idea that B (receiver) is gonna receive money from A (sender)\nbut does not know that on what address he'll be receiving, so he'll keep scanning\nthat's the only possible idea I can think of right now \n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
