      "updated": 1773298654972,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. I am going to create stealth-address for that I am \n    going to use libraries, but I don't know that does \n    Bitgo provide any libraries or API's for generating \n    those, I don't think so, \n    \n    now comes the core issue, if I create wallet address from \n    a different libraries then how come they'll be linked using \n    a Bitgo wallet? \n\n    cause the main transaction I have to do is using Bitgo  \n    so if the wallet addresses are not different, then I am \n    pretty much in trouble\n ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. I am going to create stealth-address for that I am \n    going to use libraries, but I don't know that does \n    Bitgo provide any libraries or API's for generating \n    those, I don't think so, \n    \n    now comes the core issue, if I create wallet address from \n    a different libraries then how come they'll be linked using \n    a Bitgo wallet? \n\n    cause the main transaction I have to do is using Bitgo  \n    so if the wallet addresses are not different, then I am \n    pretty much in trouble\n ",
