      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1773383114678,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. bitgo wallet setup done \n2. node js backend for stealth-public key generation (receiver)\n3. node js backend for deriving one-time addresses (sender)\n4. a library to somehow prove that the one-time address does not \n    belong the receiver's stealth public key \n5. node js backend which will scan the blockchain to check the one-time \n    address generated from receiver's stealth public key (private view key) \n6. node js backend to spend those funds from one-time address \n    using spend key (private spend key)\n7. other things: managing private keys in secure storage\n8. UI to bind all these things ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. bitgo wallet setup done \n2. node js backend for stealth-public key generation (receiver)\n3. node js backend for deriving one-time addresses (sender)\n4. a library to somehow prove that the one-time address does not \n    belong the receiver's stealth public key \n5. node js backend which will scan the blockchain to check the one-time \n    address generated from receiver's stealth public key (private view key) \n6. node js backend to spend those funds from one-time address \n    using spend key (private spend key)\n7. other things: managing private keys in secure storage\n8. UI to bind all these things ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
